   "source": [
    "## 10) Loops\n",
    "- Loops repeat code multiple times.\n",
    "\n",
    "`for` loop â†’ used to iterate over a sequence (like a list or string):\n",
    "```python\n",
    "for i in range(5):\n",
    "    print(i)\n",
    "```\n",
    "`while`loop â†’ repeats while a condition is `True`:\n",
    "```python\n",
    "count = 0\n",
    "while count < 5:\n",
    "    print(count)\n",
    "    count += 1\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "- `break` stops the loop early; `continue` skips to the next iteration."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b53491ce",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Common beginner mistakes\n",
    "- Forgetting to update the loop variable in `while` loops â†’ causes infinite loops.\n",
    "- Using `range()` incorrectly (e.g. `range(1,5)` goes 1â€“4, not 1â€“5).\n",
    "- Modifying a list while iterating over it â€” leads to unexpected results.\n",
    "- Misusing indentation (loop body must be indented).\n",
    "- Using `break` or `continue` outside of a loop â†’ causes syntax errors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a293e20c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
